# Beiza-Web — Cursor rules

## PROTECTED COMPONENTS

### Heritage page hero
Canonical frame (`HERITAGE_HERO_DEFAULTS` / `src/data/heritage-hero-canonical.json`): posX 80, posY 100, scale 111, textSide right, overlayStrength 71, copyRaiseVh 0. Protect:
- Text block RIGHT aligned (default)
- Gradient flows left (dark on the right, light on the left)
- `beiza-elder-gye-nyame-hero.png` — do not swap, do not crop
- Subject's face and Gye Nyame panel must always be visible
- "Plan your Heritage experience →" scrolls to `#consultation`
- "Already lost someone? Recover a voice →" links to `/recover`

### Beiza icon (`beiza-icon.svg` / `BeizaCircleMark`)
- **Scope:** Circle directory cards (`/circle`) only — **not** nav, favicon, Legacy shell, or enter gate.
- Path coordinates in `public/images/beiza-icon.svg` are **locked** — do not modify. Only size/position on cards (20×20, top-left).

### Circle card visual (/circle directory)
- Card top area: `/images/beiza-adinkra-stamp-hand.png` (or assigned Adinkra per `adinkra_id` when symbol assets exist)
- **DO NOT** use the stick-figure `MiniTreePreview` SVG tree on directory cards
- Warm tones — **no** grayscale filter on the card image
- Gradient overlay only: `linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0) 40%, rgba(10,10,10,1) 100%)`
- `object-fit: cover`, `object-position: center`, height `160px`, width `100%`

### Tree canvas page (/circle/[id]/tree, /legacy/circle)
- Full screen layout (100vw × 100vh) — never revert to page layout
- Header: 52px, fixed, minimal app bar
- Canvas: fills everything below header; no border, no rounded container
- No max-width containers anywhere on this route
- Fullscreen toggle must always be present on canvas controls

### Tree canvas nodes
- **`family_people` gender/career (read path):** `GET /api/circle/tree-data` does `SELECT *` on `family_people` — `gender`, `career`, and any new columns arrive in `people[]` automatically. **No changes to that API route** for reads; wire UI/types from the payload only. Writes may still need `tree-person` or Supabase updates if editable.
- **Same-session prompts:** If gender/career UI is requested together with an earlier **alt+drag** (canvas pan) prompt in one Cursor session, alt+drag is already covered — do not duplicate that work; only add gender/career display/edit from `people[]`.
- steven.oppong node with photo: DO NOT change the photo or layout
- Edge color: rgba(68,102,255,0.5) — never white or gray
- Handle color: #E6A817
- Disconnect: right-click edge → Remove connection, OR select edge + Backspace; right-click person node → Disconnect node (removes all edges for that person)
- **Group nodes:** `layoutGroupNodes` normalises child coords to `(0,0)` inside the group bbox before setting `parentId`; children use `extent: "parent"`. Parent group nodes must appear before children in the nodes array. Keyboard `G` groups selection — guard `isTypingInInput()` so typing in the edit popover does not trigger it. Save `canvas_x`/`canvas_y` as absolute positions (parent offset + child relative).
- **`onNodeDragStop`:** Read the current handler before editing. Preserve: `setPositionOverrides`, `setEdges` person-edge refresh via `treeEdgesToFlowEdges`, and `savePersonCanvasPosition`. Use `buildPersonAbsolutePositionMap` for edge refresh (not raw `node.position` when grouped). `useRef` must be imported from React for `groupStateRef`.
- **Person photo upload API:** The photo endpoint writes `photo_url` back to `family_people` in the **same request** (upload + DB update). Do **not** add a second client `PATCH` to `tree-person` after upload — use the URL returned in the photo API response and update local state / `people[]` from that.
- **New person placement:** Use `getViewport()` from `useReactFlow` for current pan/zoom, then `screenToFlowPosition()` on the viewport centre so new people land at the **visible centre** of the canvas — not at `(0, 0)`.

### AI persona (server-side)
- **`VITE_AI_PROVIDER`** is read on the **server** (Vercel API routes / `vercelApiDevPlugin` loads `.env`) — **not** in the browser. Use `process.env.VITE_AI_PROVIDER` in API handlers (works locally and on Vercel).
- **Local test:** `ollama serve` running; model pulled: `ollama pull llama3.2` (default target `llama3.2`).
- **System prompt is the most important part.** If the family has recordings with link type **`by`** that person (their own voice / prompts), those transcripts are the **foundation of the persona** — prioritize `by` links over `about` when building context.
- **Agentic loop:** `POST /api/circle/persona-chat` — Claude/Ollama may call multiple tools per turn before replying: `add_person`, `connect_people`, `update_person` (`api/lib/personaAgent.ts`, `api/lib/personaTools.ts`).
- **Canvas refresh:** When tools mutate the tree, API returns `tree_updated: true`; client dispatches `beiza:tree-updated` with `{ circleId }` — tree page refetches via `fetchCircleTreeData` (no full reload). Event: `BEIZA_TREE_UPDATED` in `src/lib/legacy/personaEvents.ts`.

### Vault screen (/legacy/vault)
- Free users CAN:
  - Record unlimited-length voice memories
  - Rename their memories
  - **SHARE** memories via link (generates `beizalegacy.com/memory/[token]` — Beiza player only, no raw download)
  - Play back recordings
- Free users CANNOT:
  - Delete recordings (locked trash icon)
  - Download raw audio files
- **Sharing is free on all tiers** — share button always active on memory cards.
- **Download raw audio** — Keeper and Heritage only.
- Upsell copy: "Download recordings as audio files" — never "Download & share" as a paid bundle.

### Patterns / health architecture (product — do not conflate layers)
Three distinct layers; the Patterns tab synthesizes across all of them:
1. **Traits = character** — personality, physical descriptors, gifts, known-for (who they were). Side panel **Traits** section; persist to `family_people` trait columns when added (today: `localStorage` interim).
2. **Health = medical** — conditions, screenings, diagnoses per person (separate from character). Built passively via **weekly question** (one answer/week → health graph over years). Not the same table/UX as career/bio.
3. **Patterns = AI synthesis** — cross-generation reasoning over traits + health + tree edges + profile fields (`career_path`, `birthplace`, `languages`, etc.). Example output: *"Three generations of hypertension on the paternal side — your father, his father, and two uncles. Consider regular blood pressure screening."*
- **Weekly question** = engine that fills the health graph without a medical intake form.
- **Warning system** = Patterns tab closes the loop: surfaced risks → actionable preventive guidance.
- **Tree profile fields** (`family_people` + persona tools) = character + lineage dataset for Patterns; every panel field save is infrastructure for the reasoning layer.
- Do not store medical data in trait tags or vice versa.

### Node data fields (tree canvas)
- All profile fields save to `family_people` on blur (panel) or context menu save.
- Right panel **Profile** section mirrors node dropdown fields — shared `peopleList` state in `FamilyTreeCircleView`.
- **Alt+drag** duplicates node with new UUID, `(copy)` suffix, +40px offset; context menu duplicate uses +60px — same `duplicateFamilyPerson`.
- **career_path** shows on node card below name (truncated 20 chars); relation label only on card when no career.
- **Disconnect node** removes all edges for that person (confirm dialog), not the node.

### Tree relationship lines
- Click a line label (e.g. **Parent of**) or right-click → **Edit relationship** to change type.
- Changing a person’s role (e.g. **CHILD** → **GRANDCHILD** in the side panel) updates all connected lines (e.g. **Parent of** → **Grandparent of**) via `relationshipSync.ts`.

### Sibling birth order (auto-layout)
- `family_people.sibling_order` — **1 = eldest** among siblings with the same `parent_id`.
- Side panel → **Birth order (siblings)** — reorder with “More eldest / More youngest”; then run **vertical/horizontal layout** on the toolbar.
- If `sibling_order` is unset, layout falls back to `birth_year` (older = further left).

### Family leader pin (tree canvas)
- **Who is leader:** `resolveTreeLeader()` in `src/lib/legacy/treeLeader.ts` — priority: (1) explicit pin `is_tree_anchor`, (2) KEEPER/SELF/ME relation, (3) most memory links, (4) first gone, (5) earliest tree member.
- Tree header shows **Leader: [name]** and reason; click opens their profile panel.
- Pin via context menu or side panel → sets `is_tree_anchor` and reorganizes layout at pin `(0,0)`.
- Leader node shows gold **Leader** badge with map pin.

### Node shape system (tree canvas)
- Ancestor/grandparent → circle 140px (`circlePerson`)
- Parent/uncle/aunt → rounded rect (`person`, default)
- Self/keeper → soft square 160px (`squarePerson`) with pulse
- Child/grandchild → circle 100px (`circlePerson`)
- Shape from `relation_label` via `getFlowNodeType` — never hardcode per person id
- Edge styles vary by `relationship_type` (`edgeStyleForRelationship`)

### Tree light / dark mode
- Toggle: **sun/moon** in header and bottom-left zoom toolbar (`TreeThemeProvider`, `beiza_tree_theme` in localStorage).
- Light mode uses `.tree-theme-light` CSS variables on `.tree-shell` — canvas, panel, chrome, nodes.

### Recording upload paths
- **`persistViaApi={false}`** (legacy `/legacy/record`): `saveRecordedMemory` → `uploadLegacyRecording` — requires **`supabase.auth.getUser()`** (logged-in legacy user).
- **`persistViaApi={true}`** (public `/circle/:id/record`): `saveRecordedMemory` → `POST /api/circle/record-memory` with circle **bearer token**; server uses **service role** for storage + `recordings` insert.
- Tree canvas and record UI use the same `persistViaApi` flag — never call `uploadLegacyRecording` from the public circle route.

### Node side panel (`PersonBiographyPanel`)
- **Memories:** Never leave "Gathering memories…" spinning forever — 4s timeout → empty state; circle route loads via `tree-data` + `recording_person_links` (not anon `get_person_biography` RPC).
- **Editing:** All profile fields inline; autosave on blur via `onProfileSave`; brief gold **Saved** flash — no save button.
- **Layout:** Sticky header (photo, name, relation); scrollable body (`overflow-y: auto`).
- **Tags:** Languages → `family_people.languages[]`; traits (known for, physical, personality, gifts) → session `localStorage` until DB columns exist.

### Node handles (tree canvas)
- Hit area: 40px × 40px (`.family-tree-handle` in `index.css`); visual dot via `box-shadow` inset ~10px, color `#E6A817` only — never blue.
- `connectionRadius={50}` on ReactFlow — snap within 50px of a handle.
- Handles visible on node hover, when selected, and when any connection drag is in progress (`.family-tree-flow.connecting`).
- Relationship picker: drag direction infers parent / child / sibling options (`treeConnectionInference.ts`); diagonal shows full picker.
- Relation chevron (`.node-relation-chevron`): visible on node hover only.

### Homepage hero (layout only)
- Full bleed (100vw) — no max-width on the outer hero shell
- Nav: 100% width, padding 0 48px (`px-12`), no max-width wrapper
- Hero copy block: max-width 680px, left-aligned, `md:pl-20` — do not change hero image asset or studio frame values
